.TH ODKRUN 1 2024-08-22 "odkrun @PACKAGE_VERSION@"

.SH NAME
odkrun - ODK Runner tool

.SH SYNOPSIS
.SY odkrun
.RB [ -h | --help ]
.RB [ -v | --version ]
.RB [ -d | --debug ]
.RB [ -i | --image
.IR name ]
.RB [ -t | --tag
.IR tag ]
.RB [ -l | --lite ]
.RB [ -s | --singulary ]
.RB [ -n | --native ]
.RB [ --root ]
.RB [ -e | --env
.IR name=value ]
.RB [ --java-property
.IR name=value ]
.RB [ --owlapi-option
.IR name=value ]
.RB [ -k | --oak-cache
.IR cache ]
.RB [ -K | --oak-user-cache ]
.RB [ seed | command ... ]
.YS

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.B odkrun
starts a ODK container and executes a command within it.

.SH GENERAL OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -h ", " --help
Display the help message.
.TP
.BR -v ", " --version
Display the version message.
.TP
.BR -d ", " --debug
Print debug informations when running.

.SH IMAGE OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -i ", " --image " " \fIname\fR
Use the specified Docker image. If not specified, the default
is to use the \fIobolibrary/odkfull\fR image.
.TP
.BR -t ", " --tag " " \fItag\fR
Use the specified image tag. If not specified, the default
is to use the \fIlatest\fR tag.
.TP
.BR -l ", " --lite
Use the \fIobolibrary/odklite\fR image.

.SH BACKEND OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -s ", " --singularity
Run the container with Singularity rather than Docker. This
is experimental but should mostly work.
.TP
.BR -n ", " --native
Run in the native system rather than in a container. This is
VERY experimental and likely not to work. This assumes that
all tools of the ODK are somehow available in the system PATH.
.TP
.BR --root
Run as a superuser within the container.

.SH PASSING SETTINGS AND DATA TO THE CONTAINER
.TP
.BR -e ", " --env " " \fIname=value\fR
Pass an environment variable.
.TP
.BR --java-property " " \fIname=value\fR
Pass a Java system property to Java programs (mostly ROBOT)
within the container.
.TP
.BR --owlapi-option " " \fIname=value\fR
Pass an option to the OWLAPI library. To list available
options, use \fI--owlapi-option=help\fR.
.TP
.BR -k ", " --oak-cache " " \fIcache\fR
Share the specified directory as a OAK cache directory
within the container. If \fIcache\fR is set to \fIuser\fR,
the user's own OAK cache directory is shared; if set to
\fIrepo\fR, the tmp/oaklib directory is shared (only if the
runner is started from within an ODK repository); any other
value is interpreted as the path to the directory to share.
.TP
.BR -K ", " --oak-user-cache
Equivalent to \fI--oak-cache=user\fR.

.SH SEEDING MODE
.PP
If the first non-option (positional) argument is \fIseed\fR,
.B odkrun
will automatically invoke the \fIodk.py seed\fR command
inside the container, and the rest of the arguments on the
command line will be passed to that command.

.SH CONFIGURATION FILE
.PP
The ODK-generated \fIrun.sh\fR script allows the use of
a configuration file (named \fIrun.sh.conf\fR) using the
syntax of the Bourne shell.
.B odkrun
will automatically attempt to parse such a file if it is
detected in the current working directory.
.PP
Lines starting with \fI#\fR are ignored. Options must be
of the form \fIKEY=VALUE\fR. The value must be enclosed
in either single or double quotes if it contains any
space.
.PP
The following options are supported:
.TP
.B ODK_IMAGE=\fIimage\fR
Equivalent to the \fI--image\fR option.
.TP
.B ODK_TAG=\fItag\fR
Equivalent to the \fI--tag\fR option.
.TP
.B ODK_SHARE_OAK_CACHE=\fIcache\fR
Equivalent to the \fI--oak-cache\fR option.
.TP
.B ODK_DEBUG=yes
Equivalent to the \fI--debug\fR option.
.TP
.B ODK_JAVA_OPTS=\fIoptions\fR
Allows passing arbitrary Java options. No equivalent
command-line options.
.TP
.B ODK_BINDS=\fI/host/path:/container/path,...\fR
Allows to bind arbitrary volumes. No equivalent
command-line options.
.TP
.B OWLAPI_\fIKEY\fR=\fIVALUE\fR
Allows to pass options to the OWLAPI. Equivalent to
the \fI--owlapi-option\fR option, but with a different
syntax.
.TP
.B ODK_USER_ID=0
Equivalent to the \fI--root\fR option.
.PP
Any other option found in the configuration file is
passed verbatim to the ODK container as an environment
variable.

